- **Base Oil Additives (Group I, Group II, Group III):** The categorization based on base oil additives such as Group I, Group II, and Group III further delineates the global pour point depressant market. Each group represents a different level of refining and purity, affecting the performance and application of pour point depressants. Group I base oils are characterized by conventional refining processes, while Group II and Group III base oils undergo more advanced refining techniques, resulting in higher quality and improved properties. The selection of base oil additives is crucial in determining the effectiveness of pour point depressants in meeting specific industry requirements.

